<br>
Perhaps I should state what my thoughts on it are...  I've thought of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>teaching</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as going line-by-line giving background info on scripture verses with some application.  Then I believed <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>preaching</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> was more like ... like an oral essay wherein you hear some background &amp; maybe word origins with a larger emphasis placed on the practical or life application.  I guess that expositional sermons fall along with that, too.<br>
<br>
Also, anyone have a definite preference for one over the other?  And are there any biblical/spiritual reasons for your preference? <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;">Expect to have hope rekindled. Expect your prayers to be answered in wondrous ways. The dry seasons in life do not last. The spring rains will come again. ~Sarah Ban Breathnach </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wordwolf>WordWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style=color:green;><b>Sir WordWolf,<br>Keeper of Odd Knowledge,<br>Bachelor-at-Arms</b></span></span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#B87333>(10/20/03 6:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=47.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sermons: Preaching versus Teaching </span><hr size=1> As it's usually practiced,<br>
