I tend to agree with your thoughts here.  Most of my denominational past has been spent in Baptist churches and so, the sermons would fall under the 'teaching' aspect.  We were expected to bring our Bibles and follow along with the pastor..taking notes and all.  I think this is a good way to learn, but not the best because there is no time for questions/different opinions and such.  I would rather do a Bible study on my own or with a group.<br>
<br>
