This is such an interesting topic for me, as I was just talking about it this a.m. with my mom.  Over the past few years-present, I am doing a 180 on my views regarding the Sunday service.<br>
<br>
I am thankful for the Orthodox Church- it's opened a new world to me on worship, praise, and peace.  It's not that I view one way 'right' and the other 'wrong', it's just that I no longer want to worship in the way that I have mostly known --long sermons/bible study type-, but rather a liturgical service, where the sermon is but one equal aspect of the entire service.<br>
